|Deity = {{ill|Ōtoshi no Kami|ja|大歳神}}, {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素盞鳴尊}}, {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山咋神}}
}}
'''Yashiro Ōtoshi Shrine''' (八代大歳神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Himeji City, Hyōgo Prefecture|ja|姫路市}}, Japan. The shrine also enshrines Iwakami Daimyōjin along with the {{ill|Toshigami|ja|年神}}.

== Overview ==
The shrine is situated at the base of Yashiroyama, north of {{ill|Himeji Castle|ja|姫路城}}. It venerates {{ill|Ōtoshi no Kami|ja|大歳神}}, {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素盞鳴尊}}, and {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山咋神}}.

== Access ==
The shrine is a 4-minute walk north of {{ill|Himeji Station|ja|姫路駅}}.

== Notes ==
{{Reflist}}

== External Links ==
* [http://www.yojnja.sakura.ne.jp/index.html Official website of Yashiro Ōtoshi Shrine]

{{Shinto-stub}}

